{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"691879f4-4be8-4a30-b2f5-a838639537ae","content":"\n\nHere's a quick overview of common choices:\n\n**ASP.NET Core** (`dotnet new webapi`)\n- `--auth Individual` – ASP.NET Identity with local accounts\n- `--auth IndividualB2C` – Azure AD B2C\n- `--auth SingleOrg` – Azure AD (single tenant)\n- `--auth MultiOrg` – Azure AD (multi-tenant)\n- `--auth Windows` – Windows/Negotiate auth\n\n**Node.js** – Express/Fastify + libraries like Passport.js, or frameworks like NestJS with `@nestjs/passport`\n\n**Python** – FastAPI with OAuth2/JWT (`python-jose`, `passlib`), or Django REST Framework with `djangorestframework-simplejwt`\n\n**Java** – Spring Boot with Spring Security (`spring-boot-starter-security` + `spring-boot-starter-oauth2-resource-server`)\n\nFor a quick start with .NET, for example:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -n MyApi\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific framework and auth type?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3e11745d-1661-4913-b0a2-6c2847a595a6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge about common web frameworks and their authentication options.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most common frameworks.","outputTokens":328},"id":"d4d8c977-74b3-4af0-a0da-8efd82a72e0d","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:45:57.354Z","parentId":"8aa00a24-311f-4eb4-83c4-da3ab5781123"}
